sql:
SELECT COUNT(line_id) AS trigger_line_count
FROM trigger_lines
WHERE created_by = 1;

SELECT line_name
FROM trigger_lines
WHERE threshold_value > 0;

external_knowledge:
- High purity in metrics often refers to the quality or accuracy of the data being collected; 
- The threshold value of 0.5 is a critical cutoff for distinguishing between significant and insignificant trigger lines; 
- A system status of 'OK' indicates that the system is functioning normally, without any warnings or critical issues.

Highly active trigger lines refer to those with an average L0 event fraction greater than 0.7; 
the primary detector refers to the detector with an ID of 0; 
a high passing rate of L0 events means an average L0 fraction greater than 0.7.

